title: M | History, Etymology, & Pronunciation | Britannica
snippet: History, etymology, and pronunciation of m, the thirteenth letter in the alphabet. It corresponds to the Semitic mem and to the Greek mu. The Semitic form may derive from an earlier sign representing waves of water. The sound represented by the letter has been from the beginning the labial nasal.

title: M - Wikipedia
snippet: M is the thirteenth letter of the Latin alphabet, derived from the Phoenician Mem via the Greek Mu. It represents the voiced bilabial nasal /m/ in many languages and has various uses in writing, numerals, units, abbreviations and logos.

title: m - Wiktionary, the free dictionary
snippet: m is the thirteenth letter of the basic modern Latin alphabet and a numeral. It has various meanings and uses in different languages and contexts, such as a symbol for meter, a prefix for milli-, and an abbreviation for meter or meter per second.
